result.name: Bubba Gump

reviews.text: Nice dining experience. Warm service. Comfortable seating. Not a big fan of deep fried so gave 3 star. Food quality is fair.

Nice dining experience, wonderful view! The thought that someone actually made the effort to turn a fantasy from a movie into an actual business proposition still amazes me. A little pricey in my opinion, so won’t envision myself going back again anytime soon.

You come here for the view. The shrimp are very good and so are the drinks but since this is a chain you are paying a premium price. Make sure to grab a spot near the window so that you can enjoy the wonderful view of the city skyline. This place is perfect for a quick appetizer or just drinks. Just make sure to get a window seat. It’s totally worth it.

Worth every penny for the experience of the view, the movie memorabilia and of course the view. Fan of the film oh not. Oh the food was pretty good too. You have to try the Alabama Sweet Smoothie (peanut butter and ice cream with a bit of chocolate). Oh wow.

Very good service and very delicious taste. Good option if you’re visiting the peak. They have nice view as well. There is also a store outside for their products. Had the shrimper’s heaven and tilapia with Cajun shrimp. Both were very delicious. The sweet was Alabama brownie which has tasty ice cream. The portions are okay but for sweet is good. The drink was strawberry mango chillers which was really chilling. We got the glass as well ( look for the star in the menu for that).

result.name: Peak Tower

reviews.text: It's gives a fantastic view of Hong Kong. Please take a good camera with you. The classic tram ride through the backwards of some of the high rise buildings is another attraction. It's a real beauty. You won't get this experience in all the best of cities.

Awesome view of Hong Kong at the top. Scary bus ride down, unfortunately the tram was undergoing upgrading work during my visit. Worth the visit if you like to have a good view of the city, try going in the evening for day and night view.

The view from here was absolutely stunning! It does take a while to get up the mountain though, no matter which form of transport you choose to take. The area was perfect for pictures especially from a tourist view point.

The scenery is outstanding. You can either take the bus or the peak tram (currently is out of function due to maintenance) to get to the peak. Best time will be when the sky is clear to get good photos and evening to see the light show from the peak which will amaze you.
Absolutely incredible views of Hong Kong. Many restaurants and shops. I recommend going in the evening, the city view us even more impressive. Definitely on the to do list if visiting Hong Kong.
